-- Irish four-year austerity plan due Wed afternoon
-- 
-- Wed Nov 24, 2010 6:20am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/11/24/us-ireland-plan-timing-idUSTRE6AN1A820101124

 

 DUBLIN  (Reuters) - Ireland's four-year austerity plan is expected to be unveiled on Wednesday afternoon, Irish media reported on Wednesday. 

 The plan will outline the detail of how the government plans to save 15 billion euros over the next four years. The Finance Ministry has yet to give an exact time for the announcement.